  <bodyText><![CDATA[<h2>Fly with Inghams comfort and convenience all the way!</h2>
<h2>Airport parking &amp; hotels</h2>
<p>Book with our partner, <a data-udi="umb://document/c1dfd7b000b545cab768de4fc23d69f3" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c1dfd7b000b545cab768de4fc23d69f3}" title="Airport Parking Hotels &amp; Lounges">APH Airport Parking &amp; Hotels</a> and <strong>get up to 35% discount</strong> at all UK Airports, Airport Hotel Offers from only £35 per person including FREE parking or Meet and Greet valet parking at Airports from only £45. For further information and online booking, see <a data-udi="umb://document/c1dfd7b000b545cab768de4fc23d69f3" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c1dfd7b000b545cab768de4fc23d69f3}" title="Airport Parking Hotels &amp; Lounges">APH Airport Parking &amp; Hotels</a></p>
<h2>Checking in</h2>
<p>Check-in desks open <strong>approximately 2-3 hours </strong>prior to departure and we recommend you check-in at least 2 hours before. Each passenger must check-in their own luggage as this is an important security check. You will need to produce your e-tickets and passports (e-tickets are checked against passports) and have your baggage weighed. Most airports no longer call out flight boarding details so you must watch the indicator board and individual TV monitors. Inghams cannot accept any responsibility for passengers who miss flights if they fail to check-in at the specified time shown on flight tickets.</p>
<h2>Online Check-in</h2>
<p>Online check-in is now available on some of our scheduled flights to Europe and North America. We will provide you with an airline locator with your e-tickets approximately 2 weeks before you travel. You will then be able to access your booking via your airline's website 24 hours before departure and pre-book your seats or check-in online.</p>
<p>Online check-in is also not available with any of our charter airlines or low cost carriers. Where seats have been pre-booked on our charter services, exact seat numbers will be provided to you at check-in.</p>
<h2>Luggage and Excess Baggage</h2>
<p>Due to weight and volume restrictions, our airline partners impose the following baggage allowances per person.</p>
<h4>Charter flights</h4>
<p>Normally 15-20kg per person (excluding infants) but varies by airline. Your allowance will be shown on your e-ticket.</p>
<h2>Low Cost scheduled flights</h2>
<p>Carriage of one piece of baggage will automatically be reserved for you.</p>
<h2>Other scheduled flights (Europe &amp; Canada)</h2>
<p>1 piece per person weighing up to 20kg (23kg on British Airways). <br />BA Club Europe &amp; World Traveller Plus and Club World have an allowance of 2 pieces per person.</p>
<p>All airlines (including charter carriers) now strictly enforce these limits and will charge for excess baggage, either per kilo or by extra piece. Please check the airlines' websites for the most up-to-date information regarding baggage allowances.<br /><br /><strong>Please note:</strong> All baggage restrictions are implemented and enforced by the airline - Inghams does not charge (or receive any revenue) for excess baggage.</p>
<h2>Hand Luggage</h2>
<p>Passengers (excluding infants) are allowed to carry ONE piece of cabin baggage on board free of charge. Handbag, briefcase, laptops, etc must be carried within your permitted 1 piece of cabin baggage. It should weigh no more than 5kg and not exceed the maximum dimensions of 55cm x 40cm x 20cm. As a guide, your carry-on bag must be able to fit either underneath the seat or in the overhead compartment.</p>
<p>Due to ongoing security restrictions, only liquids in containers of 100mls or less will be permitted through the passenger security screening points. Liquid items must be carried in a transparent re-sealable bag (about the size of a small freezer bag).</p>
<h2>Pre-book your Seating Arrangements</h2>
<p>To ensure your party sits together, you can pre-book seats on many of our featured airlines. Full details and any applicable charges for each participating airline will be sent with your travel details. Please note that seats may be separated by an aisle due to aircraft configurations. Exact seat numbers are given at check-in. Should we cancel or change your airline to one that is not part of this scheme, we will of course issue a full refund.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.austrian.com/Info/AustrianServices/SeatCategoryGuarantee.aspx" target="_blank">Pre-book your seats</a>* with Austrian Airlines up to 48 hours before departure on their website. Your contract for this service is between you and Austrian Airlines, not Inghams.<br />*Austrian charge for this service and any issues must be directed to them.</p>
<h2>Essential Medicines</h2>
<p>Essential medicines and medical equipment, eg hypodermic needles required for your holiday may be permitted onboard in larger quantities above the 100ml limit. Passengers must have a note from their GP supporting this.</p>
<h3>In-flight Catering</h3>
<p>Please check your flight tickets for full details. Meals are served on all transatlantic services. On most short-haul services within Europe a "Buy on Board" service is now offered.</p>
<h2><strong>Baby Food</strong></h2>
<p>Liquid baby food or sterilised water, sufficient for the journey, can be taken through airport security. The accompanying adult may be required to verify by tasting.</p>
<h2>Flight Supplements</h2>
<p><strong>Charter &amp; Low Cost scheduled flights</strong></p>
<p>Flight supplements may apply on certain dates and routes. You will be advised of the actual price at the time of booking.</p>
<p><strong>Other scheduled flights</strong></p>
<p>Most scheduled airlines have several different 'booking classes' for the same seat. Depending on such factors as aircraft size, day/time of departure, a variable number of seats will be available in each booking class. Airlines operate sophisticated yield management systems and are constantly updating availability and prices. Our reservations system checks for the most up-to-date position. You may therefore be offered different supplements at different times. If you book early you have the best chance of obtaining the lowest price economy class seat.</p>
<h2>Flight Upgrades</h2>
<p>If you're flying, you can upgrade to Club Class on our British Airways flights to many European and Canadian destinations, which ensures a greater luggage allowance, more legroom and dedicated check-in desks to avoid the airport queues.</p>
<p><strong>British Airways Club World</strong> from £2600 per person return (CANADA)</p>
<ul class="unIndentedList">
<li>Choosing Club World means travelling in comfort and freedom. Dedicated departure lounges and the Elemis Travel Spa (at London Heathrow) are designed to pamper you before your flight</li>
<li>The new Club World seats are bigger, wider and more comfortable than ever - complete comfort guaranteed.</li>
<li>The very best in local and international cuisine is served along with a dedicated wine cellar.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong style="font-size: 1em;">British Airways World Traveller Plus </strong><span style="font-size: 1em;">from £600 per person return (CANADA)</span></p>
<ul class="unIndentedList">
<li>For an affordable premium, enjoy the luxury of 20% more personal space than offered in economy. World Traveller with an additional seven inches legroom and a wider armchair style seat. Upgraded dining and additional amenities included.</li>
</ul>
<h4><strong>Air Canada - Executive First</strong> from £2600 per person return</h4>
<p> </p>
<h4><strong>Club Class &amp; Business Class British Airways &amp; Swiss European Services</strong> from £150 per person return</h4>
<p>Add a touch of luxury to your holiday by upgrading to Club Europe or Business Class on British Airways and Swiss scheduled flights. This upgrade offers:</p>
<ul class="unIndentedList">
<li>Special check-in desks</li>
<li>Special lounges at UK and overseas airports</li>
<li>Superior catering and complimentary drinks</li>
<li>Increased luggage allowance</li>
<li>Priority luggage handling</li>
</ul>
<p>All supplements are in addition to the return flight rate and supplements shown in the Travel Information pages.</p>
<p>Please call Reservations on 01483 79 11 11 for latest prices and availability.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><a name="connectingflights"></a></p>
<h3>Fly from your local airport</h3>
<h4><strong>Connecting Flights for Canada<br /></strong></h4>
<p><strong>British Airways via London Heathrow</strong>. Departures from Manchester, Newcastle, Glasgow, Edinburgh, Aberdeen, Leeds Bradford and Belfast to connect with British Airways transatlantic flights from Heathrow.</p>
<p><strong>KLM via Amsterdam</strong>. Departures from Aberdeen, Birmingham, Bristol, Cardiff, Edinburgh, Glasgow, Humberside, Leeds Bradford, Liverpool, Manchester, Newcastle, Norwich and Teesside to connect with KLM flights from Amsterdam - <strong>Prices on request</strong>.</p>
<p>Please note that there are a limited number of seats on these connecting flights so it is essential that you book early. All connecting flights must be added at time of booking via our Reservations Team or online when you will be given the latest flight times.</p>
<h4><strong><strong>Connecting Flights within Europe<br /></strong></strong></h4>
<p><strong>Via London with British Airways - from £75 return</strong>.<br />If you are travelling on a BA scheduled flight from Heathrow or Gatwick to Europe, we offer connecting flights from Aberdeen, Edinburgh, Glasgow, Jersey, Newcastle, Manchester, Leeds Bradford and Belfast.</p>
<p><strong>To Zurich via Amsterdam with KLM - from £99 return</strong>.<br />Connecting flights from Aberdeen, Birmingham, Bristol, Cardiff, Edinburgh, Glasgow, Humberside, Leeds/Bradford, Liverpool, Manchester, Newcastle, Norwich and Teesside to Zurich via Amsterdam.</p>
<p>If you encounter any difficulty when searching for availability, we recommend that you book Heathrow or Gatwick and then contact our Flight Operations department, send an email to our <a href="mailto:operations@inghams.co.uk">Operations department</a> quoting your confirmed booking reference and the regional airport you wish to depart from.</p>
<p> </p>
<h3>Advanced Passenger Information (API)</h3>
<p>The UK Government requires airlines to collect API for passengers on routes to and from the UK. Airlines will only provide each country's authorities with the relevant information required by them. However, some governments also require airlines to provide them with Passenger Name Records (PNR). Governments of some other countries also require API.</p>
<p>For most countries, API is restricted to the standard information contained in the Machine Readable Zone (MRZ) in machine-readable passports which can be scanned or swiped at airport check-in and transmitted to the country concerned at the time the aircraft departs. However, some countries are now requiring additional information from passengers that isn't contained in passports, or they are requiring it earlier or both. We are legally required to collect your advance passenger information. You will receive further information before your departure when and how we need to collect your details.</p>
<p>Please note that any failure to provide the required information may result in your carriage being denied. Please be assured that we have measures in place to protect the personal information you provide us (please see our <a data-udi="umb://document/744254e89e86433d968483868600b482" href="/{localLink:umb://document/744254e89e86433d968483868600b482}" title="Privacy Policy">Privacy Policy</a>).</p>
<p>More information can be found on the <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.ukba.homeoffice.gov.uk/travellingtotheuk/beforetravel/advanceinfopassengers/">home office website</a>.</p>
<p> </p>
<h2>Travel by air</h2>
<p><strong>We firmly believe your holiday begins the moment you leave home, so we have done everything we possibly can to make sure your journey to and from resort is as smooth as possible. With more regional flight departures than any other company, plus convenient resort transfers and the further options of train travel or self-drive holidays, we offer the range to ensure you can choose exactly what suits you best.</strong></p>
<p> </p>
<h3>Fly Direct From 25 UK Airports</h3>
<p>Our range of UK airports helps keep your journey times to a minimum, and for your added convenience, we can also arrange your airport car-parking or an overnight airport hotel for you in advance – see details below.</p>
<h3>Connecting Flights</h3>
<h4><strong>Via Europe</strong></h4>
<p>Inghams has negotiated special rates to selected destinations with the following European airlines:</p>
<ul>
<li>K.L.M. via Amsterdam</li>
<li>S.A.S. via Copenhagen/Oslo</li>
</ul>
<p>Flight details and full flight times will be given at the time of booking. You have a short flight from your UK airport to Amsterdam/Copenhagen/Oslo where you change aircraft before flying to your chosen destination. Your luggage is checked through to your final destination (except in Oslo, where you will have to reclaim your baggage).</p>
<h4>British Airways via Gatwick/Heathrow</h4>
<p>For a £75 supplement we can offer connecting flights to airports shown in the table above from: Aberdeen, Belfast, Edinburgh, Glasgow, Jersey, Leeds-Bradford, Manchester and Newcastle. We recommend you book early in order to get the lowest tour operator economy booking class from Gatwick or Heathrow</p>
<p> </p>
<h3>"Scheduled/Low Cost" Carriers</h3>
<p>Low cost airlines do not offer meals and drinks though sometimes these can be purchased on board. Flight baggage allowance is one piece of luggage at 20kg on Easyjet, flybe, Jet2, Norwegian and Thomson Airways. Ryanair is one piece of luggage at 15kg per person.</p>
<p> </p>
<h3>“No-Frills” Carriers</h3>
<p>No-frills airlines do not offer meals and drinks though sometimes these can be purchased on board. Flight baggage allowance is one piece of luggage at 20kg on Easyjet, flybe, Jet2 and Thomson Airways. Ryanair is one piece of luggage at 15kg per person.</p>
<p> </p>
<h3>Meals</h3>
<p>Complimentary food and beverages are continuously being reviewed by airlines and may no longer be offered free to economy class and charter flight passengers. All of our charter airlines (with the exception of Austrian Airlines) offer a ‘buy on board’ meal service.</p>
<p> </p>
<h3>Baggage Allowances</h3>
<p>All European flights (charter and scheduled), now limit each passenger to one item of checked in luggage weighing either 18 or 20kg. Exact details will be on your e-ticket</p>
<p> </p>
<h3>Pre-Bookable Seating Arrangements</h3>
<p>To ensure your party sits together, you can pre-book seats on the following airlines: Austrian Airlines and Thomson Airways (Innsbruck, Salzburg and Verona only).<br />Simply reserve your seats at the time of booking up to 12 days before departure for a small charge of £9 per person return. Please note that seats may be separated by an aisle due to aircraft configurations. Exact seat numbers are given at check in. Should we cancel or change your airline to one that is not part of this scheme, we will issue a full refund.</p>
<p> </p>
<h3>UK Airport Car Parking</h3>
<p><strong>3 GREAT OFFERS FOR YOUR CONVENIENCE</strong><br />1) Up to <strong>35% discount</strong> at all UK Airports<br />2) Special Airport Hotel Offers from only £35 per person!<br />Including FREE PARKING<br />3) Meet and Greet valet parking at airports from only £45<br />   Valet parking is ideal. Simply drive to the airport terminal where an APH representative meets you and takes your car to their nearby secure car park. On your return,         your car is then delivered back to you directly at the terminal for you to drive straight off home.</p>
<p>For full details and to book online go to <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://www.aph.com/" target="_blank">www.aph.com/inghams</a></p>
<p> </p>
<h3><strong> Business/Club Class Upgrades Start From:<br /></strong></h3>
<p><strong>SWISS INTERNATIONAL<br /></strong></p>
<p>Business class upgrade rates are:</p>
<p>Heathrow to Zurich/Geneva £170  Birmingham/Manchester to Zurich £210</p>
<p><strong>BRITISH AIRWAYS</strong></p>
<p>Why not pamper yourself?<br />Inghams can offer all clients travelling with British Airways the opportunity to upgrade. The lowest return supplements for this upgrade are as follows:</p>
